"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/dndengine"},"doc://DnDEngine/documentation/DnDEngine/DnDCoins":{"role":"symbol","title":"DnDCoins","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DnDCoins"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Common coins come in several different denominations based on the relative"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"worth of the metal from which they are made. The three most common coins"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are the gold piece (gp), the silver piece (sp), and the copper piece (cp)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"With one gold piece, a character can buy a bedroll, 50 feet of good rope,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or a goat. A skilled (but not exceptional) artisan can earn one gold piece"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a day. The gold piece is the standard unit of measure for wealth, even if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the coin itself is not commonly used. When merchants discuss deals that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"involve goods or services worth hundreds or thousands of gold pieces, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"transactions donâ€™t usually involve the exchange of individual coins."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Rather, the gold piece is a standard measure of value, and the actual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exchange is in gold bars, letters of credit, or valuable goods."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/DnDEngine\/documentation\/DnDEngine\/DnDCoins","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DnDCoins"}],"url":"\/documentation\/dndengine\/dndcoins"}}}